modules.description: This module constructs a properly formatted CoHTTP request with a multipart form body. It takes a `Multipart_form.multipart` value and returns a CoHTTP header and body pair suitable for sending HTTP requests with file uploads or form data. It is used when making HTTP POST requests with multipart/form-data content using CoHTTP.

Parses HTTP multipart/form-data requests into a structured tree and a stream of individual parts. Works with Cohttp.Request.t and Cohttp_lwt.Body.t to handle server-side form data extraction. Useful for processing file uploads or form submissions in web applications where each part may contain different data types like text fields or binary files.

Constructs and parses HTTP multipart/form-data requests for client and server operations. Works with CoHTTP headers, bodies, and multipart form data structures to handle file uploads and form submissions. Used to send properly formatted POST requests with file or form data from clients and extract structured data from incoming requests on servers.
